statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

article.headline: North Dakota 69, St. Olaf 58
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D -- Travis Bledsoe's 15 points helped North Dakota defeat Saint Olaf 69-58 on Tuesday night. Bledsoe was 3 of 5 from 3 and 6 of 10 from the field. Derek Benter added a career-high 14 points, including 6 of 7 from the free-throw line. The Fighting Sioux (2-12) were 15 of 18 (83.3 percent) from the free-throw line. The Oles (4-5) were led by Stuart Neville's 20 points and three blocked shots. Mark Torell added 19 points, making 8 of 15 shots from the field. Nate Krosschell had a game-high nine rebounds. North Dakota held a 41-31 lead at halftime. The Oles would cut the lead to three, 48-45, with 11:08 left in the game. North Dakota quickly countered with a 12-3 run over the next four minutes to extend the lead to 60-48. This was the first ever meeting between the two schools.
